Total Sales Sheet 9

1.Open a new sheet


2.  Click on Format and select shading and select sheet>worksheet and select color #e8edda


3. Drag and drop  Sales Text under Marks.

4. Right click on Sales and select Format.



5. Go to pane under Default Select Numbers ,Custom Numbers, Decimal Places 0 and Display Units as Millions Prefix as $.


6.  Click on Text and then click on the ellipses Select the Text and select Font Type : Tableau Bold >Font Size :12 Bold >  Alignment :Center .


7. Click on Alignment and select Horizontal Center and Vertical Center


8. Rt click on title and erase everything and enter Total sales. Select the Title and select  Font type Tableau Semi bold > Font size 10 > Bold > Align center
